{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit"]]},"relationshipsSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/Se","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/SE","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/SQ","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/SH","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/s8SendableP","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/s16SendableMetatypeP"],"type":"conformsTo","kind":"relationships","title":"Conforms To"}],"kind":"symbol","schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The network configuration mode for a virtual machine."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"enum","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"NetworkMode","kind":"identifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"overview","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Each mode maps to a specific "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Virtualization.framework"},{"type":"text","text":" network"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"device attachment type. The mode determines how the guest’s"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"network traffic is routed relative to the host and the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"external network."}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Choosing-a-Network-Mode","text":"Choosing a Network Mode"},{"type":"table","rows":[[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Mode","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Guest → Internet","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Host → Guest","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Entitlement","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode\/nat","isActive":true,"type":"reference"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"✓","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Via resolved IP","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"None","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode\/bridged(interface:)","isActive":true,"type":"reference"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"✓","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Own LAN IP","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"com.apple.vm.networking"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode\/isolated"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"✗"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"✗"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"None"}]}]]],"header":"row"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For host-guest communication without full network access,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"use "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode\/isolated"},{"type":"text","text":" mode and communicate via the VirtIO socket"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"device ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"VZVirtioSocketDeviceConfiguration"},{"type":"text","text":"), which is always"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"attached regardless of network mode."}]},{"type":"aside","style":"note","name":"Note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Bridged mode requires the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"com.apple.vm.networking"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"restricted entitlement, which must be requested from Apple"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Developer Technical Support."}]}]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"anchor":"Why-There-Is-No-Host-Only-Mode","text":"Why There Is No Host-Only Mode"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Apple’s Virtualization framework provides three network"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"attachment types: "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"VZNATNetworkDeviceAttachment"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"VZBridgedNetworkDeviceAttachment"},{"type":"text","text":", and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"VZFileHandleNetworkDeviceAttachment"},{"type":"text","text":". None of these"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"implements host-only semantics directly."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A host-only mode would require a user-space virtual network"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"switch built on top of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"VZFileHandleNetworkDeviceAttachment"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"handling raw Ethernet frames, DHCP, and packet routing — a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"substantial subsystem that would need its own lifecycle"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"management and security hardening. Rather than ship a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"half-baked implementation or silently fall back to NAT"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(which would give VMs unintended internet access), this enum"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"only exposes modes that the Virtualization framework supports"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"natively."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you need isolated host-guest communication, use "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode\/isolated"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"with the VirtIO socket device. If you need full IP networking"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"between VMs, use "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode\/bridged(interface:)"},{"type":"text","text":" on a dedicated"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"host-only network interface."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode\/bridged(interface:)","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode\/isolated","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode\/nat"],"generated":true,"title":"Enumeration Cases","anchor":"Enumeration-Cases"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode\/init(from:)","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode\/init(serialized:)"],"generated":true,"title":"Initializers","anchor":"Initializers"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode\/serialized"],"generated":true,"title":"Instance Properties","anchor":"Instance-Properties"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode\/encode(to:)"],"generated":true,"title":"Instance Methods","anchor":"Instance-Methods"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode\/Equatable-Implementations"],"generated":true,"title":"Default Implementations","anchor":"Default-Implementations"}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode"},"sections":[],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/networkmode"]}],"metadata":{"fragments":[{"text":"enum","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"NetworkMo